        "summary": "Incyte announced 24-week long-term data from its Phase 3 TRuE-AD4 trial evaluating Opzelura (ruxolitinib) cream in adults with moderate atopic dermatitis. The data, presented at the 2026 EADV Symposium, showed that the majority of patients who achieved EASI50 at Week 8 maintained disease control through Week 24 when using Opzelura as-needed. Specifically, 84.3% achieved EASI75 and 70.6% achieved IGA-TS at Week 24. The treatment was well-tolerated with no new safety signals.",
